	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Retrobright an old SNES?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have had a SNES and Dreamcast turn yellow just by sitting in the closet with no possible UV exposure. I've read that oxygen in the air reacts with the fire retardants in the plastic over time, causing the discoloration, with UV only speeding up the process.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


